summary: An Ode to Tied Together With A Smile
title: An Ode to Tied Together With A Smile
body:
Thank you for writing Tied Together With A Smile, Taylor. When I’m having a tough time, I listen to it because it’s very therapeutic. It speaks to my soul more than you could ever know. I have experienced all the emotions you describe in it without being able to verbalize them. I am so grateful for this song. The speech you gave before you performed it last night was beautiful.


Growing up disabled and even in adulthood, I always felt the pressure that I couldn’t be like everyone else and Tied Together With A Smile really resonated with me because I feel that way all the time.

summary: When you’ve been a fan of Taylor Swift’s music ever she came out, but you mainly only listened to the singles for the most part....
body: When you’ve been a fan of Taylor Swift’s music ever she came out, but you mainly only listened to the singles for the most part. So you go back through her discography and listen to the songs you never really listened to before. And you discover songs like Dear John, All Too Well, Better Than Revenge, Holy Ground, Stay Stay Stay, etc., and it’s like she just released a couple new albums because you have so much “new” music to go through…
